            "body": "You're right that they're running `0` (since that's the \"default value\" for the numeric types).\r\n\r\nHowever, typically we'd use `-1` as an error code for numeric types \r\n\r\nMy proposed change here was to make fused functions use the usual `-1` error code. (A PR doesn't yet exist). The problem would be that you couldn't assume `-1` for functions that came from a pxd file because they might have been generated with an earlier version of Cython.",
